<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Make a Smoker</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Out of Aluminum</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="circumstance">Once summer comes around</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="joint">you want to sit outside with friends</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="joint">and do something fun ,</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1004" relname="joint">like have a barbecue !</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="span">Unfortunately , buying a barbecue smoker could be pretty expensive ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="purpose">so why not make one at home ?</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="preparation">In this wikiHow , you &apos;ll learn just how to do that !</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Get all the materials .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="span">There &apos;s a list at the bottom of the article under the Things</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">You &apos;ll Need section .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="preparation">Luckily , most of these things can be found at your local home improvement retailer !</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="condition">If something ca n&apos;t be found ,</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="contrast">then you can probably ask a friend</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1016" relname="contrast">or order it online .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1018" relname="preparation">Prepare the oil drum .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1019" relname="span">Make sure that your drum does n&apos;t contain anything</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="19" relname="elaboration">that could cause a problem , like flammable liquids , for example .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="attribution">After you have made sure</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1022" relname="span">that your oil drum is safe ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="elaboration">you will want to strip the paint off with the angle grinder .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1024" relname="span">Make sure you are wearing your eye and face protection at this point !</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1027" relname="condition">If you do n&apos;t know how to check for flammable liquids ,</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="joint">it is best to speak to a professional</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">and have them make sure your oil drum is safe</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="purpose">to work with !</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1029" relname="span">Create the Chimney for the Smoker</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="sequence">Cut your steel tubing at a 45-degree angle ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="span">and then twist the portion 180 degrees</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="purpose">to weld it back on .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="span">Make sure the weld is all the way around the tubing ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="33" relname="purpose">so you have a good seal .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="preparation">Make a lid .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1035" relname="joint">Create some dimensions with your measuring tools for the lid now ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1035" relname="joint">and mark them with the permanent marker .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1037" relname="sequence">Make sure the oil drum is stable</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="span">and then use your angle grinder with a cutting disk here</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="purpose">to cut along the lines .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="preparation">Weld the lid onto the drum</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1041" relname="joint">Weld your strips of steel sheeting onto the oil drum .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1041" relname="joint">This will add stability</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1041" relname="joint">and let the lid rest in place when closed .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">Clean the inside of the BBQ</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="span">The main goal</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="same_unit">for cleaning the inside</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">is not</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="purpose">so it can be spotless ,</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1051" relname="preparation">but for two reasons :</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="same_unit">1 )</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="condition">If it is not clean of oil</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="span">the paint will not stick .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="same_unit">2 )</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="condition">If the oil is there</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="57" relname="condition">once you start it</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1056" relname="span">it will emit thick black smoke .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1060" relname="span">Remove the grease</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="58" relname="means">by using a de-greaser .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1062" relname="span">You can use the same one</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="60" relname="elaboration">you use for your oven</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="elaboration">or you can buy one at any supermarket .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1064" relname="preparation">Fabricate the collapsible frame</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1065" relname="span">A collapsible frame consists of two rectangles</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="elaboration">that will fold inside of each other .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1064" relname="joint">Using a hacksaw ,</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1068" relname="span">cut a length ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1069" relname="sequence">you decide the size ,</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1070" relname="joint">and then you will weld the two triangles</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="joint">and make sure they are right angles .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1072" relname="sequence">The second step is to know where the center of each is located</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1072" relname="sequence">and you can drill in holes ,</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="sequence">size does not matter ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1072" relname="sequence">and this is where the frames will hinge .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1077" relname="span">After you have put the two parts together</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1078" relname="span">you will now need to position the frame correctly</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="76" relname="purpose">so the oil drum can be on top of it .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1080" relname="span">An obstacle</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1081" relname="same_unit">you might run into</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1081" relname="same_unit">is preventing the frame from falling ,</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1082" relname="span">so you may have to use a string</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="81" relname="purpose">to keep the pieces together .</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1084" relname="same_unit">Then</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="85" relname="condition">when you are done</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1085" relname="span">the frame will close .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1087" relname="preparation">Attach hinges to the lid</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1087" relname="joint">You will need nuts and bolts for this step .</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="1087" relname="joint">For this step , you will need to place your hinges correctly</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1090" relname="span">and to do that you should use a permanent pen</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="89" relname="purpose">to mark the spots of the hinges .</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="1092" relname="preparation">Add the safety edging</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="1092" relname="joint">You will need to add the safety edging in sharp areas of the lid and oil drum .</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="1094" relname="span">A tip is to do it on the inside</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="93" relname="purpose">so it can also hide the welds .</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="1096" relname="preparation">Attach the handle</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="1097" relname="span">You will need a handle</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="96" relname="elaboration">fabricated from steel .</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="1096" relname="joint">Weld the handle in the middle of the lid .</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="1101" relname="span">Make sure to remove all the little pieces of metal</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="99" relname="elaboration">created</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="1101" relname="elaboration">from cutting the steel .</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="1103" relname="preparation">Add the grill supports and hooks</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1104" relname="span">Weld two bars of steel for the main grill and other two for the smoker grill ,</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="103" relname="elaboration">with all of them going through the extension of the oil drum .</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="1106" relname="span">At the bars &apos; tips of the main grill , weld another piece of steel</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="105" relname="purpose">to form a hook on both sides .</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="108" relname="circumstance">When placing the bar ,</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="1108" relname="span">be certain that the holes from left side to right side are aligned .</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="1111" relname="span">Weld 3 small hooks on one side of the drum</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="109" relname="purpose">to form holders for BBQ`s tools .</segment>
<segment id="111" parent="1112" relname="span">Drill a hole in the lid for temperature dial ,</segment>
<segment id="112" parent="1113" relname="span">drill two large holes on each side of the oil drum</segment>
<segment id="113" parent="1114" relname="joint">for ventilation ,</segment>
<segment id="114" parent="1116" relname="span">and several small ones in the middle of the drum</segment>
<segment id="115" parent="114" relname="elaboration">( on the bottom )</segment>
<segment id="116" parent="1115" relname="same_unit">for drainage .</segment>
<segment id="117" parent="1103" relname="joint">Create the grill .</segment>
<segment id="118" parent="1103" relname="joint">Weld the steel mesh with the safety edgings .</segment>
<segment id="119" parent="1120" relname="span">Make sure the material of your mesh is stainless steel</segment>
<segment id="120" parent="119" relname="purpose">in order to avoid bits of rust in your food .</segment>
<segment id="121" parent="1103" relname="joint">Finish the smoker .</segment>
<segment id="122" parent="1103" relname="joint">Now you have successfully made the grill !</segment>
<segment id="123" parent="1123" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="124" parent="1124" relname="preparation">Some quick safety tips</segment>
<segment id="125" parent="1125" relname="preparation">when welding are :</segment>
<segment id="126" parent="1125" relname="joint">Always wear proper face sheilds .</segment>
<segment id="127" parent="1126" relname="sequence">Always close-toed shoes .</segment>
<segment id="128" parent="1126" relname="sequence">Always wear a long-sleeved , non-flammable shirt .</segment>
<segment id="129" parent="1126" relname="sequence">Always wear proper welding gloves .</segment>
<segment id="130" parent="1130" relname="span">Always wear proper ear protection</segment>
<segment id="131" parent="130" relname="elaboration">( to prevent sparks from entering your ear canal ) .</segment>
<segment id="132" parent="1132" relname="span">NEVER weld near an area</segment>
<segment id="133" parent="132" relname="elaboration">that was cleaned with chlorinated hydrocarbon like brake-cleaner .</segment>
<segment id="134" parent="1134" relname="span">When combined with UV light and chlorinated hydrocarbon</segment>
<segment id="135" parent="1135" relname="span">it creates a toxic gas</segment>
<segment id="136" parent="135" relname="elaboration">that can cause sever injuries or death .</segment>
<segment id="137" parent="138" relname="circumstance">When buying your oil drum</segment>
<segment id="138" parent="1137" relname="span">you must decontaminate the drum .</segment>
<segment id="139" parent="1139" relname="span">You can sanitize your oil drum</segment>
<segment id="140" parent="139" relname="means">by following these simple steps :</segment>
<segment id="141" parent="1141" relname="span">Empty as much material out of the drum</segment>
<segment id="142" parent="141" relname="circumstance">as possible .</segment>
<segment id="143" parent="1143" relname="span">Add absorbents or adsorbents bentonite , kitty litter</segment>
<segment id="144" parent="1144" relname="span">to take up any free oil</segment>
<segment id="145" parent="144" relname="elaboration">left in the drum .</segment>
<segment id="146" parent="1146" relname="span">Things You &apos;ll Need</segment>
<segment id="147" parent="146" relname="elaboration">An MIG Welder and some wire</segment>
<segment id="148" parent="1148" relname="preparation">An angle grinder , along with some cutting disks , sanding disks , and grinding disks</segment>
<segment id="149" parent="1149" relname="preparation">Hammer</segment>
<segment id="150" parent="1150" relname="preparation">Hacksaw</segment>
<segment id="151" parent="1151" relname="preparation">Engineer &apos;s square</segment>
<segment id="152" parent="1152" relname="preparation">Ruler</segment>
<segment id="153" parent="1153" relname="preparation">Tape measure</segment>
<segment id="154" parent="1154" relname="preparation">Permanent pen</segment>
<segment id="155" parent="1155" relname="preparation">Drill</segment>
<segment id="156" parent="1156" relname="preparation">Some drill bits</segment>
<segment id="157" parent="1157" relname="preparation">Center punch tool</segment>
<segment id="158" parent="1158" relname="preparation">Oil drum</segment>
<segment id="159" parent="1159" relname="preparation">High-temperature barbecue paint</segment>
<segment id="160" parent="1160" relname="preparation">Steel hinges</segment>
<segment id="161" parent="1161" relname="preparation">Chrome coach hook</segment>
<segment id="162" parent="1162" relname="preparation">Barbecue temperature dial</segment>
<segment id="163" parent="1163" relname="preparation">Mild Steel box section</segment>
<segment id="164" parent="1164" relname="preparation">6 millimeter Mild Steel round bar</segment>
<segment id="165" parent="1165" relname="preparation">U section safety edging</segment>
<segment id="166" parent="1166" relname="preparation">Strips of steel sheet</segment>
<segment id="167" parent="1167" relname="preparation">Stainless steel grill or stainless steel mesh</segment>
<segment id="168" parent="1168" relname="preparation">Nuts and bolts for the hinges and frame</segment>
<segment id="169" parent="1169" relname="preparation">Large Steel tubing for the chimney</segment>
<segment id="170" parent="1169" relname="span">Safety protection</segment>
<segment id="171" parent="170" relname="elaboration">( optional , examples are gloves , a face mask , and goggles )</segment>
